  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Introducing the MikroTik wAP Series",
      "text": "Enhance your networking capabilities with the MikroTik wAP series, a versatile line of devices designed to address varied connectivity requirements. These devices excel at outdoor installations, whether on your house's exterior, porch or even mounted on a vehicle. Its weatherproof design ensures resilience against rain, snow, and extreme temperatures, providing unwavering and reliable wireless connectivity regardless of the weather conditions. With strategically placed outdoor access points, coverage range becomes virtually limitless, ideal for expansive outdoor spaces, remote locations, or areas where traditional indoor access points might falter."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Responsive Connectivity Everywhere",
      "text": "The MikroTik wAP ac LTE6 kit stands out for its dual-band proficiency, seamlessly operating on both 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz frequencies. This dual-band capability is a pivotal feature, optimizing network performance by adeptly managing multiple devices concurrently. Elevating its capabilities further, the kit incorporates CAT6 LTE support, unlocking advanced LTE functionalities that deliver impressive download speeds of up to 300 Mbps. This speed ensures it meets the demands of modern applications, guaranteeing a seamless and responsive user experience. The wAP ac LTE6 kit masterfully combines dual-band capabilities with CAT6 LTE support, making it a versatile solution adaptable to various use cases, including home networks, business environments, and outdoor installations in remote areas."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Enhanced Network Reliability",
      "text": "Encased in the weatherproof wAP form factor, this device is designed for versatile deployment, suitable for both indoor and outdoor settings. The form factor's flexibility allows mounting on walls, ceilings, poles, or flat surfaces. Two Gigabit Ethernet ports ensure efficient data transfer for scenarios where wired connections are preferred or required. Designed to operate within a wide temperature range from -30°C to +60°C, this device demonstrates robust temperature tolerance, making it suitable for deployment in diverse climates. Its adaptability extends to both cold and hot environments, ensuring consistent and reliable functionality. A standout feature is the inclusion of LTE backup capabilities through the Micro SIM slot. In case of primary wired connection failure, the device seamlessly transitions to LTE, ensuring uninterrupted internet connectivity. This LTE backup functionality significantly enhances the reliability of the network, critical for continuous connectivity in various environments."
    }
  ],
